      <bioghist id="aspace_2c1cb5ca1e937314a909020bffe3131f">
         <head>Stephen O. Saxe</head>
         <p>Stephen O. Saxe (1930-2019) was a graduate of Harvard College and Yale Drama School. His first career was as a set designer, working for summer stock and in television. He later worked as a book designer and graphic artist for Harcourt Brace. After retiring, Saxe devoted himself to the study of letterpress printing, and was a founding member of the American Printing History Association.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_96a86bd3e83f33b362963f5053f81141">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. Set and costume designs, 1925-1963. II. Photographs, 1936-1993. III. Other papers, 1949-1981.</p>
      </arrangement>
